low the Real Living Wage.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","208376"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041409","Wales Office","false","2019-01-17","<p>Ministers and civil servants in my Department have regular discussions with No 10 colleagues on a range of issues.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041409/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-17T11:41:42.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041409/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041409/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2019-01-14","Wales Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what discussions his Department had with the Prime Minister's office on the content of the Prime Minister's Brexit speech in Stoke-on-Trent on 14 January 2019.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","208210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041410","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-01-22","<p>The Care Quality Commission (CQC), Health Education England (HEE), the Health Research Authority, the Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency (MHRA) and NHS England comply with minimum wage legislation and pay all directly employed staff at levels at or above the National Living Wage.</p><p> </p><p>All London employees of the CQC, HEE, the HRA, the MHRA and NHS England earn the London Living Wage.</p><p> </p><p>The CQC has 290 employees outside London earning less than the London Living Wage.</p><p>HEE has 229 employees outside London earning less than the London Living Wage.</p><p>The HRA has 21 employees outside London earning less than the London Living Wage.</p><p>The MHRA has three employees outside London earning less than the London Living Wage.</p><p>NHS England has 282 employees outside London earning less than the London Living Wage.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041410/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-22T15:33:34.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041410/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041410/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-01-14","Department of Health and Social Care: Public Bodies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many staff at (a) Care Quality Commission, (b) Health Education England, (c) Health Research Authority, (d) Medicines and Healthcare Products Regulatory Agency and (e) NHS England that work (i) inside and (ii) outside Greater London are paid at a rate below the London Living Wage.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","208377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041411","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-01-22","<p>The Care Quality Commission (CQC), Health Education England (HEE), the Health Research Authority, the Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency (MHRA) and NHS England comply with minimum wage legislation and pay all directly employed staff at levels at or above the National Living Wage.</p><p> </p><p>The CQC, HEE, the HRA, the MHRA and NHS England have no staff in London who earn below the Real Living Wage.</p><p> </p><p>The CQC has 73 employees earning below the Real Living Wage outside of London.</p><p>HEE has 0 employees earning below the Real Living Wage outside of London.</p><p>The HRA has 0 employees earning below the Real Living Wage outside of London.</p><p>The MHRA has 0 employees earning below the Real Living Wage outside of London.</p><p>NHS England has five employees earning below the Real Living Wage outside of London.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041411/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-22T15:32:19.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041411/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041411/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-01-14","Department of Health and Social Care: Public Bodies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many staff at (a) Care Quality Commission, (b) Health Education England, (c) Health Research Authority, (d) Medicines and Healthcare Products Regulatory Agency and (e) NHS England that work (i) inside and (ii) outside Greater London are paid at a rate below the Real Living Wage.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","208378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041412","Cabinet Office","false","2019-01-22","<p>The Boundary Commission for Northern Ireland is sponsored by the Northern Ireland Office, not the Cabinet Office, and I cannot therefore provide an answer to point (b) in each of your questions.</p><p> </p><p>No staff at the (a) Boundary Commission for England, (c) Crown Commercial Service, (d) Government Property Agency and (e) Privy Council Office working inside Greater London are paid at a rate below the London Living Wage of £10.55 per hour.</p><p> </p><p>At the Crown Commercial Service, 18 staff working outside Greater London are paid at a rate below the Real Living Wage of £9.00 per hour.</p><p> </p><p>No staff in the other bodies mentioned working outside Greater London, are paid at a rate below the Real Living Wage of £9.00 per hour, and all staff are paid above the National Living Wage of £7.83 per hour.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041412/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-22T15:29:53.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041412/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041412/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-01-14","Cabinet Office: Public Bodies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many staff at the (a) Boundary Commission for England, (b) Boundary Commission for Northern Ireland, (c) Crown Commercial Service, (d) Government Property Agency and (e) Privy Council Office (i) inside and (ii) outside Greater London are paid at a rate below the London Living Wage.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","208379"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041413","Cabinet Office","false","2019-01-22","<p>The Boundary Commission for Northern Ireland is sponsored by the Northern Ireland Office, not the Cabinet Office, and I cannot therefore provide an answer to point (b) in each of your questions.</p><p> </p><p>No staff at the (a) Boundary Commission for England, (c) Crown Commercial Service, (d) Government Property Agency and (e) Privy Council Office working inside Greater London are paid at a rate below the London Living Wage of £10.55 per hour.</p><p> </p><p>At the Crown Commercial Service, 18 staff working outside Greater London are paid at a rate below the Real Living Wage of £9.00 per hour.</p><p> </p><p>No staff in the other bodies mentioned working outside Greater London, are paid at a rate below the Real Living Wage of £9.00 per hour, and all staff are paid above the National Living Wage of £7.83 per hour.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041413/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-22T15:30:48.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041413/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041413/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-01-14","Cabinet Office: Public Bodies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many staff at the (a) Boundary Commission for England, (b) Boundary Commission for Northern Ireland, (c) Crown Commercial Service, (d) Government Property Agency and (e) Privy Council Office (i) inside and (ii) outside Greater London are paid at a rate below the Real Living Wage.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","208380"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041414","Treasury","false","2019-01-22","<p>The administration of the tax system, including where appropriate the repayment of tax or duties, is a matter for HMRC. It would not be appropriate for Ministers to become involved in the administration of the tax system in specific cases.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041414/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-22T15:39:22.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041414/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041414/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-01-14","Roadchef: Employee Benefit Trusts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, when HMRC plans to reach an agreement with the Roadchef Employee Benefit Trust on outstanding tax issues.","false","Biography information for Karin Smyth","Bristol South","Karin Smyth","208381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041415","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-01-22","<p>I have asked the CEO of each organisation to write to the hon. Member on this matter, and copies of these letters are attached.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041415/answer","Attachment to 208382.pdf ; Attachment to 208383.pdf","Attachment to 208382.pdf ; Attachment to 208383.pdf","Chief Executive Letters ; Letters from Chief Executives","Chief Executive Letters ; Letters from Chief Executives","208383","2019-01-22T14:11:51.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041415/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1041415/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-01-14","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Public Bodies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many staff at (a) Companies House, (b) the Insolvency Service, (c) the Intellectual Property Service (d) the Met Office and (e) the UK Space Agency (i) inside and (ii) outside Greater London are paid at a rate below the London Living Wage.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","208382"
