"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038363","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-01-14","<p>The Department does not hold this information. BT gainshare/clawback was built into all of the Superfast contracts. This has been re-invested into a number of recent Superfast contracts and change requests. However those contracts and change requests also included a blend of other funding from BDUK, Local Bodies, Suppliers, ERDF and EAFRD. Furthermore in many cases those contracts have consisted of a mixture of Fibre to the Cabinet and Fibre to the Premise. Therefore it is difficult to determine a one to one correlation between clawback and Full Fibre connections.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038363/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-14T16:09:25.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038363/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038363/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-01-09","Broadband: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate he has made of the number of additional full fibre broadband connections in rural areas which will be provided using capital contributions clawed back from BT in connection with its BDUK projects.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","206713"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038364","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-01-15","<p>Natural England attends the annual Wildlife Panel for the Malvern Hills where it is presented with a summary bird report for the area for the year. The last panel was held in March 2018 and Natural England will attend the next meeting in March this year. In the meantime Natural England continues to liaise with members of the group.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038364/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-15T17:34:45.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038364/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038364/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-01-09","Birds: Malvern Hills","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 21 November 2018 to Question 191481 on Birds: Malvern Hills, which bird groups Natural England has met with; and when Natural England propose to next meet with those bird groups.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","206849"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038365","Cabinet Office","false","2019-01-14","<p>The membership of and terms of reference for the Advisory Military Sub-Committee will be published on gov.uk when they have been finalised, and agreed by incoming members.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038365/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-14T17:05:28.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038365/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038365/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-01-09","Committee On the Grant of Honours Decorations and Medals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, when he plans to publish the independent membership and terms of reference of the Advisory Military Sub-Committee of the Honours and Decorations Committee.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","206850"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038367","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-01-11","<p>The estimate can be found on page 24 of the Child Maintenance Compliance and Arrears Strategy consultation document which was published in December 2017</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/667033/child-maintenance-compliance-arrears-consultation.pdf" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/667033/child-maintenance-compliance-arrears-consultation.pdf</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038367/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-11T10:40:36.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038367/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038367/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-01-09","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate she has made of the amount of debt to be written-off from arrears accrued under the Child Support Agency because parents had not responded to (a) letters and (b) telephone calls within 60 days.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","206851"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038368","Department for Transport","false","2019-01-17","<p>Highways England have undertaken an in-depth safety review of the A34 to identify incident ‘hot spots’ and to establish their causes.</p><p>They have made their recommendations to the Department of Transport on a package of safety improvements for the A34. The improvements remain on track for the start of works in 2019/20. As with all such schemes, the package remains subject to a positive value for money assessment at the end of the development process, before the start of construction.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038368/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-17T14:32:16.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038368/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038368/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-01-09","A34: Oxfordshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to improve safety on the A34 in Oxfordshire.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","206852"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038369","Department for Transport","false","2019-01-17","<p>The scheme referred to is currently under consideration as part of Network Rail’s Control Period 6 portfolio.</p><p> </p><p>As the National Audit Office have said, it is right to continually assess the investment decisions in our programme of railway upgrades, to deliver passenger benefits in the best way possible and give both passengers and taxpayers maximum value.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038369/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-17T14:57:54.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038369/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038369/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-01-09","Cherwell Valley Railway Line: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 7 September to Question 167383 on Cherwell Valley Railway Line: Electrification, when he expects the publication of the timetable for a decision to be made on the future electrification of the railway line between Oxford and Didcot Parkway.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","206853"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038370","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-01-17","<p>Information on the cost to the Foreign and Commonwealth Office for President Trump's Guest of Government visit will be published on the gov.uk website in the next few weeks.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038370/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-17T16:31:55.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038370/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038370/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-01-09","USA: State Visits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 5 December 2018 to Question 196147 on USA: State Visits and with reference to his Department's data Costs relating to State and Guest of Government visits, when information relating to the July 2018 visit to the UK of US President Donald Trump will be published on the gov.uk website.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","206775"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038372","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-01-15","<p>The Department has had regular engagement with Parliamentary colleagues and industry to discuss energy policy matters, including on tidal energy.</p><p>Since 2003 the Government has made £174m innovation and grant funding available to wave, tidal stream technologies (£80m of that since 2010). As set out in the Clean Growth Strategy, wave, tidal stream and tidal range technologies could have a role in the long-term decarbonisation of the UK, but they will need to demonstrate how they can compete with other forms of generation.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038372/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-15T14:57:10.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038372/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1038372/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-01-09","Tidal Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps his Department (a) has taken and (b) plans to take to promote tidal power schemes since the decision was taken not to fund the Swansea Bay Tidal Lagoon project.","false","Biography information for Luke Graham","Ochil and South Perthshire","Luke Graham","206854"
